public FileDocument(java.lang.String filename)
Constructs new file document.

The instance is created with default content type set to APPLICATION_OCTET_STREAM.

Parameters:
filename - [in] full filename (path + filename) of the file.

FileDocument

public FileDocument(java.lang.String filename,
                    ContentType contentType)
Constructs new file document with specific content type.

It is highly discouraged to use enumerated values from @see ContentType for textual content such as XML. In fact, ContentType.APPLICATION_XML force charset to ISO-8859-1.

Parameters:
filename - [in] full filename (path + filename) of the file.
contentType - [in] content type of the file.
